We first calculate the average owner’s equity over the period. From the balance sheet we have:

• Beginning Owner’s Equity = 16,000,000.00  
• Ending Owner’s Equity = 16,099,532.29  

Average Owner’s Equity = (16,000,000.00 + 16,099,532.29) / 2  
               = 32,099,532.29 / 2  
               ≈ 16,049,766.15  

The net profit from the income statement is 99,532.29.

Return on Equity (ROE) is computed as:  
  ROE = (Net Profit / Average Owner’s Equity) × 100

Plugging in the values:  
  ROE = (99,532.29 / 16,049,766.15) × 100  
     ≈ 0.0062033 × 100  
     ≈ 0.62%

Thus, the ROE is approximately 0.62%.
